espnW is a voice for the woman who loves sports. Founded in July 2010, espnW lives across television, films, events, digital and social platforms. To connect with the W audience on a deeper digital level by building brand awareness and loyalty throughout the summer, an integrated social media campaign was created. 98 Days To Shine put the fans in the spotlight from Memorial Day to Labor Day via daily photo challenges, DIY projects, motivational quotes and athlete integration. Results: 8,812 user generated photos were submitted during the 98-day campaign. The hashtag #98DaysToShine reached over 16 million social users. espnWs social footprint increased by 24% on Twitter and 7,500% on Instagram. The achievements of the 98 Days to Shine photo challenge were celebrated with the Summer of W Finale event, a gallery showcase featuring the best entries from the photo challenge in the heart of NYCs NoLIta district.
