<hr />
&nbsp;
I\'ll save you my list of fun facts, quirky jobs and countries I\'ve visited, written in third person. To paint a picture of what it was like to work with me, here it is. I\'m on time 99% of the time. Persuading people to help me deliver the best work possible without being a jerk comes naturally. I\'m a talker and a doer. Small groups, strong relationships and being elbows deep in an agency and a brand (or three) is where I thrive. That requires hard work, initiative, photoshop skillz and type-A-like tendencies. I fight to craft memorable creative without losing it\'s integrity through the tumbler of client feedback, budget restrictions, research, timing, politics and other unpredictable forces. I believe with the kind of hours we keep doing this, it\'s important to laugh a lot and pet animals.
&nbsp;
As a child, standing atop a \"high dive,\" I learned to perform fearlessly in front of a crowd and deliver high scores. My work has been mentioned in the likes of Adweek and AdAge to The New York Times and Fox News, with industry awards from an Emmy, to an Effie, and to an Obie.
